8. (Anonymous Functions) Explain how you can create an anonymous function to be used immediately or stored for later use.

Functions are defined using the "function" keyword which has the following syntax:

function Name(parameters){
  //body
}

Name(arguements); // calling the function

To create an anonymous function, simply omit the name.
To call the function, place the entire function in parenthesis, and then follow it with the function invoction operator, which also uses parenthesis.

(function(parameters)
{
  // body
})(arguements);

To save the anonymous function for later use, store it in a variable

var func = function(parameters){
  //body
};

func(arguements);
